rComments: Tracy is amazing. She's so passionate about writing, which definitely shines through in her lessons. Tracy usually prepares thought-provoking readings for each class, and discusses everything from the feelings they evoke to the structures they utilize. I left Tracy's class feeling inspired and empowered to write, and I think my peers felt the same.

As an international student from Singapore who had Professor Moniz from 2009-2010 (I think that was the year I was taking Journalistic Investigation at UTM). Professor Tracy has been instrumental with her lectures, experiences, realism and her focus to care for the writing standards for her students. She pushes students to work harder!
She is so inspirational and you will learn so much about writing from her. She is a tough prof, but it's all worth it.

Tracy is a hard marker and makes you work for a good grade, but I haven't learned as much useful information, and remembered it, from anyone else in 4 months. Probably the one of the few only amazing professors out there. The textbook readings are so uselful

EXCELLENT!! She is clear, concise, informative, and captivating! She will hold the class's attention and is very passionate about her craft. She does mark hard but its warranted. Her feedback is helpful! Writing is a lost art that 90% of working "professionals" should have mastered! It also helps that Tracy is extremely easy on the eyes!! :P
She teaches well but expects highly professional work. The course required a lot of hard work but I guess it was good preparation for a career in journalism.
Ok proff but extremely hard marker. Avoid her if possible. TAke tallman
